\paragraph{Title Credits}

Certain credit must, and others may, appear in the title information associated
with the registration of the ISBN.
The credits here are not necessarily the same as credits shown on the cover or the
interior of the book, but are used in the pages used on amazon and {\createspace} web sites.

It is desirable I think to keep the credits shown here to a moderate number,
which in the case of the {\Product} manuals suggests that not all contributors to
a manual need be listed.

The following table is compiled using git shortlog to determine the
number of commits, and a certain amount of common sense
(major contributions may be introduced by a single commit,
and the reference manuals are compiled primarily from information
stripped from dtds and therefore a log of the top level document
is misleading as to the origins of the bulk of the material).

The codes used in the table have the following significance:

\begin{description}
\item[A] Principal Author
\item[a] Author
\item[C] Contributions by
\item[I] Index by
\item[P] Prepared for publication by
\item[S] Series Editor
