\section{TEST POLICY}\label{TEST POLICY}

After review of inputs for publication (as specified above), the relevant data will be submitted to {\createspace}.
An automatic check will be made of the interiors, and any issues raised will be addressed.
At this point cover images will also be made available for review by Lemma1.

All title information must be correct at this point since it cannot be changed after submission for review by {\createspace}.
The titles are then submitted for review by {\createspace}.
After submission for review, electronic proofs will be available, and it will be possible to print proofs.
It is not anticipated that printed proofs will normally be obtained, but this could be done it it was thought desirable.

If any issues are found in the electronic or printed proofs, or if any late information requiring amendments arises 
then alterations can still be made.
If this is done the amended manuals will have then to be resubmitted for review by {\createspace}.

Once {\createspace} and lemma1 both concur the manuals can be published.

Certain further items of information must be agreed between Lemma1 and its publishing agent at this time,
viz. the channels for publication and the list prices.
However, these can be changed subsequent to publication.

In order to ensure that the purchasor is properly informed about the version of the manuals available in print,
the target release of {\Product} ({\TargetPPRel}) is show in the descriptions supplied on publication and are shown in this document.
If the title changes suggested are not incorporated by  that release, then the publication of the manuals will have to be
deferred untill they are (or this proposal modified accordingly), and the version numbers shown here and filled into the {\createspace}
forms will have to be changed.

